---
description: graphify knowledge graph context (when graphify-out exists)
alwaysApply: true
---

This repo can use **graphify** outputs under `graphify-out/` after you run `graphify` on the codebase (CLI: `graphify` from the `graphifyy` PyPI package, e.g. `pipx install graphifyy`).

**When `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` exists**

- Prefer reading `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` before very broad architecture questions (god nodes, communities, suggested questions).
- If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, use the wiki as a navigation index instead of rereading large raw areas blindly.

**Keeping the graph fresh**

- After meaningful code edits in an area that is already graphed, run `graphify update .` when you want the code graph refreshed (AST-oriented update path; see graphify docs for limits).

**If outputs are missing**

- Run `/graphify .` (or `graphify` CLI on the repo root) once to generate `graphify-out/`. Until then, skip graph-specific steps and use normal code search.
